CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 28, 1960, pg. 2, reads: "Duff St. Club Succeeds - Believing that the city was neglecting their community, residents of Duff St. organized a block club and began vigorously protesting... On the right is another condition typical of the ones which the club is protesting. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Pile of garbage and rubble, including mattress and three barrels, next to garage and parked car, in front of brick apartment building, possibly Duff Street, Hill District
